      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2020-01-28</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2020-02-27T20:50:42Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Helping Emergency Responders Overcome Act of </b><b>2020</b> <b>or the HERO Act of 2020</b></p> <p>This bill establishes a series of programs relating to the behavioral health of public-safety officers (e.g., law-enforcement officers, firefighters, ambulance crew members, and 911 operators). For example, the bill establishes (1) a public-safety officer suicide-reporting system at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, and (2) a grant program for peer-support behavioral health and wellness programs within fire departments and emergency medical services agencies. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
